      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "ROLL ON COASTER (1) was strongly fancied last time but ran below expectations when fifth (20.65), beaten 12 lengths. Goes well out of this box with a win and three minor placings. Can make amends. ZIPPING FONTANA (2) was safely held last time out, finishing fifth at Angle Park over 342m behind Binnaway Wizard (20.26) in a Grade 5. Form from her last run is proving to be solid. Key player if finds best. WEBLEC SNIP (4) showed little early speed at his last couple, the latest finishing fourth (31.29) in a Grade 3/4/5 at Angle Park. Solid record here winning two races. One of the better hopes. OUR LAURA ROSE (6) is worth another chance despite missing the top-three here most recently.",
